### How I Applied It
I find that the topic of reimagining an angle for the same picture using AI very interesting. I have found 1 model and 2 spaces that explores this idea while I was searching through Hugging Face. The model is called fal/Qwen-Image-Edit-2511-Multiple-Angles-LoRA, and it outputs the content of an image being shown at a different angle based on your input references using apparently, LoRA adapter. The spaces do pretty much the same thing, and they're called Qwen-Camera-Angles-Rethink and Qwen-Image-Edit-Angles. I didn't get the model to work since I have no idea of how to extract the code from the website. For the spaces, I input a picture of a bee on a flower and a picture of a goat standing on a mountain, and I input to turn the angle 90 degrees to the right for both spaces. 

### What I Expected
I expected both of the spaces to mess up the general shape of the animals in the picture, since it can be hard for the Al models to handle the details of the picture, and it can be hard for them to tell which object in the picture needs to be blurred. For example: the flower in the bee picture needs to be blurred since the main part of the photo is the bee. 

### What I Found
For the Qwen Camera Angles Rethink, It did a pretty good job on eachh of the pictures, but the only thing missing is that it made one of the bee's legs larger for that photo in the output. Also for the goat picture, it made the fur of the goat longer than the original. For the Qwen Image Edit Angles, everything went super smooth, but for the rocks on the mountain in the goat picture, it apparently did not know what to do when it comes to the textures of the rocks: they're just chaotic is all. 

